lcsh_terms.name: Library of Congress Subject Headings
lcsh_terms.description: Library of Congress Subject headings describing this object. To add a new heading simply type the first few letters of the heading and choose the desired one from the displayed list of possible matches.

href.name: href
href.description:
refers to a hypertext reference that provides a link to another electronic
            resource.

pref.name: pref
pref.description:
indicates that a particular data value is the preferred value when multiple
            data values for the same element or subelement exist.

refid.name: refid
refid.description:
refers to id numbers or codes coming from the local institution or resource
            named in the source attribute.

rules.name: rules
rules.description:
refers to any data content standards used to construct the value recorded in
            the element (e.g. AACR2, CCO).

source.name: source
source.description:
refers to the local, print, or electronic source from which information is
            derived for a specific element (e.g. Grove Dictionary of Art).

vocab.name: vocab
vocab.description:
refers to the controlled vocabulary source from which the term or phrase is
            recorded (e.g. AAT, LCSH)

culturalContextSet.name: Cultural context
culturalContextSet.description: The name of the culture, people (ethnonym), or adjectival form of a country name from which a Work, Collection, or Image originates, or the cultural context with which the Work, Collection, or Image has been associated.

inscriptionSet.name: Inscription
inscriptionSet.description:
All marks or written words added to the object at the time of production or in its subsequent history, including signatures, dates, dedications, texts, and colophons, as well as marks, such as the stamps of silversmiths, publishers, or
printers. The position/location of this text or symbol should be specified. If a translation of the text into the language of the catalog record is also provided, include in a repeated element with the text type of translation.

materials.name: Material
materials.description: The medium or substance of which a work or an image is composed and the production or manufacturing processes, techniques, and methods incorporated in the fabrication or alteration of the work or image.

rightsSet.name: Permissions & Rights
rightsSet.description:
Information about the copyright status and the rights holder for a work,
            collection, or image. The optional notes sub-element may include any justifications,
            conditions, or restraints on use, contact or licensing information, or other
            intellectual property statements as may be desired.

sourceSet.name: Source Set
sourceSet.description: A reference to the source of the information recorded about the work or the image. For a work record, this may be a citation to the sole source of the information recorded in a catalog record. For an image, it may be used to provide information about the supplying agency, vendor or individual.

textrefSet.name: TextRef Set
textrefSet.description:
Contains the name of a related textual reference and any type of unique
            identifier that text assigns to a Work or Collection that is independent of any
            repository.

location.name: Location
location.description: The geographic location and/or name of the repository, building, site, or other entity whose boundaries include the Work or Image.

description_text.name: Description
description_text.description: A free-text note about the physical nature, subject matter, historical context, biographical context, or interpretation, as is relevant to whatever you are describing, whether it is an object in the collection, or a person.  For items with inscriptions, stamps, signatures, or any other marking, record this information here. If any text is a quotation, please cite the source of information.  Cite any other sources including books, websites or interviews which provided information.
